This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By the end of 2019, women, girls and boys, particularly those in rural indigenous areas, access comprehensive package for health, nutrition and Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH), to guarantee the healthy growth and development, in particular during the child's first 1,000 days (from conception to 2 years of age), and to prevent and reduce chronic malnutrition and morbidity/ mortality.

description.narrative: The the Sustainable Total Sanitation and Hygiene (SAHTOSO) approach was tested and is being institutionalised and scaled up, involving national and municipal authorities.UNICEF provided technical assistance to finalise and implement the National Communication Strategy for Social and Behaviour Change at local levels.; UNICEF also developed a diploma course for designing municipal communication plans for social and behaviour change, with 575 community participants completing the course.A system to monitor changes in knowledge, attitudes and practices was designed and is now being used to consolidate information. In 27 municipalities, UNICEF promoted alliances between local radio and the COMUSAN. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:27/01/2022
